3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the coefficients describing the dependence of video quality on packet loss and delay variation, which is related to information theory. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with video streams and their quality, which is a key aspect of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, but these aspects may be relevant in the context of wireless networks and video transfer.
